from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:   # --- py stmt 2
    eor, n = 0, len(nums)   # --- py stmt 3
    for i in range(1, n + 1):   # --- py stmt 4
        eor ^= i ^ nums[i - 1]   # --- py stmt 5
    diff = eor & (~eor + 1)   # --- py stmt 6
    a = 0   # --- py stmt 7
    for i in range(1, n + 1):   # --- py stmt 8
        if (nums[i - 1] & diff) == 0:   # --- py stmt 9
            a ^= nums[i - 1]   # --- py stmt 10
        if (i & diff) == 0:   # --- py stmt 11
            a ^= i   # --- py stmt 12
    b = eor ^ a   # --- py stmt 13
    for num in nums:   # --- py stmt 14
        if a == num:   # --- py stmt 15
            return [a, b]   # --- py stmt 16
    return [b, a]   # --- py stmt 17
```

const findMissingAndDuplicateNumbers = (numbers) => {   // --- py stmt 2
    let xorSum = 0;   // --- py stmt 3
    let n = numbers.length;   // --- py stmt 3
    for (let i = 1; i < n + 1; i++) {   // --- py stmt 4
        xorSum ^= i ^ numbers[i - 1];   // --- py stmt 5
    }
    let diff = xorSum & (~xorSum + 1);   // --- py stmt 6
    let missingNumber = 0;   // --- py stmt 7
    for (let i = 1; i < n + 1; i++) {   // --- py stmt 8
        if ((numbers[i - 1] & diff) == 0) {   // --- py stmt 9
            missingNumber ^= numbers[i - 1];   // --- py stmt 10
        }
        if ((i & diff) == 0) {   // --- py stmt 11
            missingNumber ^= i;   // --- py stmt 12
        }
    }
    let duplicateNumber = xorSum ^ missingNumber;   // --- py stmt 13
    for (let num of numbers) {   // --- py stmt 14
        if (missingNumber == num) {   // --- py stmt 15
            return [missingNumber, duplicateNumber];   // --- py stmt 16
        }
    }
    return [duplicateNumber, missingNumber];   // --- py stmt 17
}
